hackathon-description-text: HackTCNJ is happening on February 24th at 10am, to the 25th at 3:30pm. It is a great place to be creative, to learn, and to develop your iPhone app, Alexa skill, or chrome extension. We want people of all skill levels, from the complete beginner who wants to make their his steps in tech, to the person who has a thousand starts on her GitHub repo.
hackathon-eligibility: If you are under 18, please have a parent or guardian sign your minor consent form. The form can be found on our website after you register.
hackathon-rules:
By registering & attending, you agree to the following policies:
MLH's Data Sharing Notice
MLH's Privacy Policy
MLH's Contest Terms and Conditions
MLH's Code of Conduct
We partner with Major League Hacking (MLH) as a MLH Member Event. By registering & attending you authorize us to share certain application/registration information for event administration, ranking, MLH administration, and occasional messages about hackathons in line with the MLH Privacy Policy.
If you will be a minor at any time during the event, you must have your guardian sign the Minor Participation Waiver.
 
Submission times will be announced soon.

hackathon-prizes.prize-content: Prize for best technical achievement. Winners receive an Amazon Echo Dot.
Prize for funniest hack. Winners receive a $50 Netflix subscription.
Prize for best first hackathon project. Winners receive a drone.
Prize for best hack using a .tech domain. Winners receive a bit coding robot.
hackathon-prizes.prize-title: Radix Best Hack using a .tech Domain

hackathon-prizes.prize-content: Prize for the best hack that educates users on a topic. Winners receive a Google Home and Chromecast.
Prize for best hack that addresses a social issue.
hackathon-prizes.prize-title: Google Techmaker General Social Good Hack

hackathon-prizes.prize-content: Prize for best hack that helps improve accessibility for the differently abled and disadvantaged. Winners receive a Google Home and Chromecast.
Prize for best hack using Twilio API.
hackathon-prizes.prize-title: Twilio Best Hack using Twilio API

hackathon-prizes.prize-content: Prize for best hack using hardware. Winners receive an Arduino kit.
Prize for best hack related to healthcare.
